<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-02T12:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-02T12:36:00-05:00" n="652" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d652">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2859</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-02T11:00:00-06:36">
                                        <hi rend="italic">October 2, 1918, 11 a.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7.50 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1570. Department’s circular September 20, 6 p.m. Foreign Office
                                replies that Mexican Government has instructed its diplomatic agents
                                    <pb facs="0774" n="700" xml:id="pg_700"/> to report as to the
                                true situation in Russia. As soon as these reports are received and
                                if the case merits, Mexican Government will consider what attitude
                                it should adopt in evidence of its sympathy for the Russian
                                people.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>